1. d4 Nf6 2. c4 g6 3. g3 Bg7 4. Bg2 O-O 5. Nc3 d6 6. Nf3 c6 7. O-O Bf5 {
A solid approach. Black intends to secure a spot for his knight in the centre,
similar to 6...Nc6 and 7...Bf5.} 8. Ng5 $5 {I found this rare move to be very
challenging - White is going to fully seize the centre with tempo.} d5 {
This is the best reaction to White's last aggressive move. Black aims to
consolidate the situation in the centre.} ({Too passive is} 8... e5 9. d5 c5 ({
After} 9... cxd5 10. Nxd5 Nxd5 11. Bxd5 Nc6 12. Ne4 Kh8 13. b3 {White has a
clear positional advantage due to the full control over the light squares.}) (
9... h6 {, as in Kollars,D - Lubbe,M Lueneburg 2016 can be well met by} 10.
dxc6 $1 Nxc6 11. Nge4 Nxe4 12. Nxe4 Bxe4 13. Bxe4 $14 {, and White's advantage
is undeniable.}) 10. e4 Bc8 11. f3 Na6 12. Nh3 Bd7 13. Nf2 Rb8 {We have been
following the game Banusz, T - Almasi, Z Ajka 2019 In my opinion, White had no
reasons for deviating from the most tempting} 14. f4 $5 exf4 15. Bxf4 Ne8 16.
Qd2 $16 {Black's position is very cramped.}) ({The most common} 8... h6 {
also runs into} 9. e4 Bg4 10. f3 Bd7 ({Equally bad is} 10... Bc8 11. Nh3 c5 12.
dxc5 dxc5 13. e5 Nfd7 14. f4 Nc6 15. Be3 $16 {Khademalsharieh,S - El Taher,F
Sharjah UAE 2019}) 11. Nh3 e5 12. Be3 Na6 13. Qd2 Kh7 14. Nf2 Qe7 15. Rad1 $16
{White was firmly in a control in Vakhidov,J - Gormally,D Hastings 2018}) 9.
Qb3 Qb6 10. cxd5 Qxb3 11. axb3 cxd5 12. Nxd5 Nxd5 13. Bxd5 Nc6 14. e3 h6 15.
Nf3 ({The other retreat seems less promising:} 15. Ne4 Rfd8 16. Nc3 e5 17. dxe5
Bxe5 18. e4 Bh3 19. Rd1 Bg4 $44 {Svane,R - Efimenko,Z Berlin GER 2019}) 15...
Rfd8 16. Bxc6 $146 {This new continuation unbalances the position. White gives
up the powerful light-squared bishop but damages Black's pawn structure.} ({
After} 16. Bc4 Be4 17. Ne1 e5 18. f3 Bd5 {Black had enough play for the pawn
in Gustafsson, J - Raghunandan, K Cha-Am THA 2018}) 16... bxc6 17. Ra5 Bd3 (
17... Rdb8 {leads to approximately the same type of positions:} 18. Bd2 Rxb3
19. Bc3 $14) 18. Re1 Rdb8 19. Bd2 Rxb3 20. Bc3 {Black's pawn structure is
dicey and the bishop pair only partly compensates for it.} *

