Qc3 Kg8 21. Bh6 Ne6 22. Re1 {The weakness of the dark squares around Kg8 still
causes Black certain problems.}) 13. Be3 a4 ({The quieter} 13... Qe7 {does not
offer Black real counterplay:} 14. Rad1 a4 ({Of course, not} 14... Nfxe4 $2 15.
Nxe4 Nxe4 16. Bxe4 Qxe4 17. Bd2 $18) ({Too passive is} 14... Nfd7 15. b3 h5 16.
f4 Qf8 17. Bf2 Ne6 18. Nde2 $16 {Black's position was very cramped in Bocharov,
D - Apicella,M Internet 2002}) 15. f4 $1 {It turns out that now White can
start extending without any further preparation.} Nfd7 (15... Nfxe4 {is
connected with a dubious queen sacrifice:} 16. Nxe4 Nxe4 17. Bxe4 Qxe4 18. Bf2
