19. Nf3 Ra3 {This was Greenfeld,A - Koneru,H Lippstadt 2004 Now the simple} 20.
Bxc5 $146 dxc5 21. e5 {[%cal Gc3e4] , followed by Nc3-e4 would have put Black
in a very difficult situation.}) 18. Qa2 Nc7 19. Qf2 {White had a slight, but
long-lasting positional advantage in Bachmann,B - Hildebrand,G email 2010}) ({
Quite popular is} 13... Nfd7 {, but it doesn't offer Black any adequate
counter-play:} 14. b3 Qb6 ({equally bad is} 14... Qe7 15. Rad1 Ne5 16. f4 Ned7
17. Bf2 Nb6 18. Nf3 $16 {Markus,R - Sredojevic,I Kragujevac 2016}) 15. Rab1 Ne5
16. Red1 Qc7 17. f4 Ned7 18. Bf2 $16 {Vaulin,A - Hausner,I Zlin 1995}) 14. Rad1
Qa5 15. Bf4 $1 {The attack on the Pd6 comes in time, so Black cannot complete
