Nf3 Nbd7 7. O-O e5 8. e4 exd4 9. Nxd4 Re8 (9... Nc5 10. h3 Re8 11. Re1 {
is just a transposition.}) 10. h3 a6 11. Be3 Rb8 12. b3 c5 {The most
consistent - Black insists on b7-b5, even though the d6-pawn is really weak
now.} ({After} 12... Nc5 13. Qc2 Bd7 14. b4 Ne6 15. Nb3 $1 {White manages to
retain all merits of his setup, while Black's position is cramped. For
instance,} Qc8 ({Better is} 15... b5 16. c5 dxc5 17. bxc5 b4 18. Nd5 {, even
though White still retains the initiative.}) 16. Kh2 b5 17. c5 {White was much
better in Matlakov,M - Adhiban,B Wijk aan Zee NED 2018}) ({After} 12... Ne5 13.
a4 Bd7 14. Ra2 Qc8 15. Kh2 {Black has difficulties to create counter-play.}) ({
