16. Rad1 Ne5 {This was Nedilko,V - Golubev,M Odessa 2006 Now the most
energetic way of handling the position was} 17. Qd2 $146 Rbd8 18. Bg5 Rd7 19.
f4 Nc6 20. f5 {, and Black is practically paralyzed.}) 14. Qxd6 b4 15. Na4 $1 {
Definitely the best. This choice is connected with a positional sacrifice.} ({
Weaker is} 15. e5 Nh5 16. f4 bxc3 17. g4 Nxf4 18. Bxf4 c2 19. Rac1 Bb7 {
with mutual chances Petrosyan,T - Iordachescu,V Al Ain 2015}) 15... Nxe4 16.
Bxe4 Bxa1 {Accepting the challenge is the best decision.} ({In case of} 16...
Rxe4 17. Rad1 Qe8 18. Nf4 Bf8 ({Even worse is} 18... Be5 19. Qc6 Bd4 20. Nxc5
$18 {Drozdovskij,Y - Golubev,M Odessa 2007}) 19. Qc7 Rb7 20. Qc6 {The absence
of the light-squared bishop did not tell, since Black was almost paralyzed in
Cheparinov,I - Schmaltz,R Berlin 2015}) 17. Rxa1 Rxe4 18. Nxc5 Re8 (18... Rb6
$6 19. Qd3 Qf6 {as in Haessel,D - Vasudeva,T Freemont 2012 can be well met by}
20. Nxe4 $1 $146 Qxa1+ 21. Kg2 Re6 22. Nf4 Re8 23. Nd6 {, and Black's position
is ruined.}) 19. Rd1 {The nasty pin leaves Black no choice, so he has to trade
queens.} Qe7 20. Qxe7 Rxe7 21. Nf4 $1 {It turns out that liquidating into the
endgame did not solve his problems. White's pieces still dominate over the
board.} Nxc5 22. Bxc5 Re8 (22... Rd7 {is hardly an attractive option either:}
23. Nd5 Kg7 24. Bd4+ f6 25. Bxf6+ Kf7 26. Be5 Rb6 27. Rd4 $16 {Black was
doomed to passive defence in Kiss,A - Tratar,M Austria 1996}) 23. Nd5 Re2 {
We have been following the game Fridman,D - Chigaev,M Batumi 2018 At this
moment I mostly like the following way of extending initiative:} 24. Nf6+ $146
Kg7 25. Bd4 Kf8 ({Hardly better is} 25... Kh6 26. Ng8+ Kh5 27. Be3 $36) 26. g4
$1 {This quiet move illustrates that White is firmly in a control!} h6 27. Kf1
Re6 (27... Rxa2 $2 28. Be5 $18) 28. f4 Rb7 29. Kf2 $36 {Black's material
advantage is of symbolic value since his rooks can hardly move and the king is
